Jaj Bl Hamed w Tum (Baked Chicken with Lemon & Garlic)
  --Vian Alnidawi and Sara Nassr

1 medium onion, cut in half, julienned
2 large russet potatoes, cut into wedges
4 chicken legs
7 tbsp olive oil, divided
1 tbsp kosher salt (or to taste)
5 garlic cloves, grated
2 lemons, juiced, ~1/3 c of juice

Preheat oven to 350F. In a large mixing bowl, toss onions, potatoes, and chicken legs with the salt and 5 tbsp of olive oil. Arrange the onion and potato pieces evenly across a deep baking tray, then place the chicken legs on top. Bake for 1 hr. In a small mixing bowl, whisk together the garlic, lemon juice, and the remaining 2 tbsp of oil. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Remove the baking tray from the oven; the chicken should be brown and crispy. Spread the lemon mixture on top, then return tray to the oven for 8 min. Serve.
